Step C7a — Case Resolved branch
When the mapping row exists with a non-null Target BU. We pull that BU GUID, stash it in varBPOwningBU, write it to the Parent BP's pei_owningbu field, and increment the Resolved counter.
Where exactly
Inside Route BP Mapping State → Case Resolved. Click the + / Add an action there. We'll add three actions in sequence inside this case.

C7a-1 — Set varBPOwningBU from mapping
What to add
Action: Variable → Set variable
Configure
Rename via "..." → Rename:
Set varBPOwningBU From Mapping
Name (dropdown):
varBPOwningBU
Value — click into field, switch to fx, paste:
first(outputs('Find_BP_Mapping')?['body/value'])?['_pei_targetbu_value']
(Pulls the single mapping row's Target BU raw GUID into the per-iteration scratch variable. We've already classified this case as Resolved so we know this value is non-null.)

C7a-2 — Update Parent BP with Owning BU
What to add
Action: Dataverse → Update a row
Configure
Rename via "..." → Rename:
Update BP Owning BU
Table name:
Parent Business Processes
Row ID — click into field, switch to fx, paste:
first(outputs('Get_BP_After_Upsert')?['body/value'])?['pei_businessprocessid']
(This is the GUID of the BP we're currently iterating on — fetched in C2.)
Click "Show advanced options" and find the Owning BU field. Click into it, switch to fx, paste:
concat('/pei_businessunits(', variables('varBPOwningBU'), ')')
About this format: Dataverse lookup writes require this OData binding format — slash, plural-collection-name of the target table, parens around the GUID. The plural collection name for the Business Unit table is pei_businessunits (note the s). This is the same pattern used in the existing Update App actions for pei_owningbu writes — if you see them and the table name suffix differs, copy that exactly.
Leave all other fields blank — we're only writing the one column.

C7a-3 — Increment Resolved counter
What to add
Action: Variable → Increment variable
Configure
Rename via "..." → Rename:
Increment Resolved Counter
Name (dropdown):
varBPOwningBUResolved
Value:
1

Save and verify Case Resolved
Save the flow.
Verify before saying "done"

 Inside Route BP Mapping State → Case Resolved, three actions in this order:

 Set varBPOwningBU From Mapping (Set variable, varBPOwningBU = first(...)?['_pei_targetbu_value'])
 Update BP Owning BU (Dataverse Update a row, target = Parent BP, Row ID = first(...)?['pei_businessprocessid'], Owning BU = concat-binding)
 Increment Resolved Counter (Increment varBPOwningBUResolved by 1)


 Flow saved without errors

Watches:

Same internal-name watch as before for Find_BP_Mapping and Get_BP_After_Upsert — if they error, substitute the real internal names from Settings.
The Owning BU lookup binding format is the most common slip. If the Update action errors at runtime with something like "InvalidLookupReference" or "binding format invalid", the issue is almost always missing the leading slash or wrong table-collection name (pei_businessunits plural with s, not pei_businessunit singular).

Reply "done" when verified. Then C7b (Case Unmapped, one action) and C7c (Case NotFound, two actions).
